description.narrative: (Ethiopia): In the last year of this HEAL TB award, USAID will focus on sustainability of regional TB programs in program leadership and management, quality DOTS services for early detection and case management, collaborative TB/HIV activities, early detection and management of drug resistant TB and health systems strengthening (HSS). Focus will be given to improving health worker skills; referral linkages; laboratory and diagnostic capacity, including scaling up of GeneXpert diagnosis; drug supply management; M&E; and operations research. In coordination with the MOH and private sector, the activity aims to achieve a TB case detection rate of 75% and treatment success rate of 90%, and to enhance MDR-TB case detection to identify at least 70% of MDR-TB cases and ensure treatment. Activities will be strengthened to achieve 100% HIV testing in TB patients and management of co-infected patients. Support will cover all Amhara and Oromiya regions reaching an estimated population of 54 million.
